Uses of Package
com.pandora.general.objects

Packages that use com.pandora.general.objects
Package
Description
com.pandora.general.objects
This package contains classes representing various objects used in the Pandora biogeochemical model for freshwater systems.
com.pandora.general.objects.builders
This package contains builders for creating instances of various objects related to the Pandora project in the context of biogeochemistry and freshwater studies.
com.pandora.general.objects.services.abstractions.classes
Provides abstract classes for services related to biogeochemistry and freshwaters in PANDORA.
com.pandora.general.objects.services.abstractions.interfaces
This package contains a set of interfaces defining abstractions for various services related to freshwater biogeochemistry within the Pandora framework.
com.pandora.general.objects.services.implementations
This package contains service implementations for managing various aspects related to freshwater biogeochemistry within the Pandora model.
com.pandora.general.services.calculation.implementations
Implementation classes for services related to calculations in PANDORA.
com.pandora.general.services.calculation.interfaces
This package contains service interfaces for various calculations in the Pandora model simulation.
  • Classes in com.pandora.general.objects used by com.pandora.general.objects
    Class
    Description
    AbstractBaseObject
    The AbstractBaseObject is an abstract class providing a base structure for objects with a unique identifier (id) and a name.
    Cell
    The Cell class extends AbstractBaseObject and represents a geographical cell with a unique identifier, name, and additional properties such as center latitude, center longitude, surface area, and the identifier of the next cell in the sequence.
  • Classes in com.pandora.general.objects used by com.pandora.general.objects.builders
    Class
    Description
    PandoraTimestep
    The PandoraTimestep class represents a specific time step in the Pandora model, characterized by initial values, start and end times, dimensionality, discharge, volume, terrestrial and upstream sources, and other properties.

  • Classes in com.pandora.general.objects used by com.pandora.general.services.calculation.implementations
    Class
    Description
    Cell
    The Cell class extends AbstractBaseObject and represents a geographical cell with a unique identifier, name, and additional properties such as center latitude, center longitude, surface area, and the identifier of the next cell in the sequence.
    CellTimestep
    The CellTimestep class extends AbstractBaseObject and represents a specific time step associated with a geographical cell.
    PandoraTimestep
    The PandoraTimestep class represents a specific time step in the Pandora model, characterized by initial values, start and end times, dimensionality, discharge, volume, terrestrial and upstream sources, and other properties.
    River
    The River class extends AbstractBaseObject and represents a river entity characterized by a unique identifier, name, and a list of independent cell sets associated with the river.
